    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_3692454905" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3692454905" />
    <a title="Iulia" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/50950278-iulia"><img alt="Iulia" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1523874313p2/50950278.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3692454905?book_show_action=true">Dec 14, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Iulia" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Iulia" href="/user/show/50950278-iulia">Iulia</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/50950278-iulia?shelf=popsugar-2020">popsugar-2020</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/50950278-iulia?shelf=read-2020">read-2020</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3692454905" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer15594145110812094704">This was my first foray into the universe of Discworld and Terry Pratchett&apos;s brand of witty humor and, let me tell you, it was an excellent experience. <a href='https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/386372.Mort__Discworld___4__Death___1_' title='Mort (Discworld, #4; Death, #1) by Terry Pratchett' rel='nofollow noopener'>Mort</a> is brilliant, entertaining, and meaningful, with a hilarious premise (Death taking on a gangly and awkward boy as an apprentice) and set on the iconic flat planet of Discworld, famously standing on the backs of four elephants, which in turn are on the back of a giant turtle, the Great A&apos;Tuin. Already sounds epic, right? The story itself is g</span>
  <span id="freeText15594145110812094704" style="display:none">This was my first foray into the universe of Discworld and Terry Pratchett's brand of witty humor and, let me tell you, it was an excellent experience. <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/386372.Mort__Discworld___4__Death___1_" title="Mort (Discworld, #4; Death, #1) by Terry Pratchett" rel="nofollow noopener">Mort</a> is brilliant, entertaining, and meaningful, with a hilarious premise (Death taking on a gangly and awkward boy as an apprentice) and set on the iconic flat planet of Discworld, famously standing on the backs of four elephants, which in turn are on the back of a giant turtle, the Great A'Tuin. Already sounds epic, right? The story itself is genuinely funny and full of little humorous gems, not-too-unkind satire, and clever social commentary. For lovers of British humor, this book is a must. </span>
  <a data-text-id="15594145110812094704" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


