<div id="review_365763204" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/365763204" />
    <a title="Phrynne" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/8655084-phrynne"><img alt="Phrynne" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1609359173p2/8655084.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/365763204?book_show_action=true">Jul 10, 2012</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Phrynne" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Phrynne" href="/user/show/8655084-phrynne">Phrynne</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/8655084-phrynne?shelf=5000-2021">5000-2021</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer365763204" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer409978061567233390">This was a reread of one of my favourite <a href='https://www.goodreads.com/author/show/1654.Terry_Pratchett' title='Terry Pratchett' rel='nofollow noopener'>Terry Pratchett</a> books so of course I have to give it five stars. Any of his Death books go straight to the top of my &apos;best of&apos; lists. <br/><br/>There is no logic to any of Pratchett&apos;s books but there is always an imaginative story, brilliant characters and lots of humour. Whether you like his books or not depends mostly on your sense of humour and I love them so I guess that says something about me!<br/><br/>I was going to say that Death is my favourite of all Pratchett&apos;s ch</span>
  <span id="freeText409978061567233390" style="display:none">This was a reread of one of my favourite <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/author/show/1654.Terry_Pratchett" title="Terry Pratchett" rel="nofollow noopener">Terry Pratchett</a> books so of course I have to give it five stars. Any of his Death books go straight to the top of my 'best of' lists. <br /><br />There is no logic to any of Pratchett's books but there is always an imaginative story, brilliant characters and lots of humour. Whether you like his books or not depends mostly on your sense of humour and I love them so I guess that says something about me!<br /><br />I was going to say that Death is my favourite of all Pratchett's characters but then I remembered Rincewind and Granny Weatherwax and Sam Vines and Vetinari and Carrot, and realised I just enjoy them all. So sad that this author has gone but at least he left a huge body of work and a lot of pleasure for readers behind him.</span>
  <a data-text-id="409978061567233390" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


